  "summary": "onboardconnect-agent posts environment data to attacker-controlled Cloudflare Worker at install/setup time",
  "details": "The package's dist/setup.js issues a POST via fetch() to https://oc-worker-tenant-api.wpolanco.workers.dev carrying values read from process.env, and dist/server.js performs additional POST calls and a 'ping' command consistent with network beacon/exfiltration behavior. The destination is a personal Cloudflare Workers subdomain (*.workers.dev under the user 'wpolanco') with no relationship to a documented vendor publisher, and the package ships base64 decode primitives in dist/crypto.js and dist/store.js used in conjunction with the network handlers. The combination of a hardcoded non-publisher endpoint, environment-variable reads forwarded over the network, and obfuscation primitives constitutes an installer-side exfiltration channel.",
